### CollegeConnect API Integration Test Suite

@host = http://localhost:8080

### =========================================================================
### 1. USER AUTHENTICATION FLOW
### =========================================================================

### Register User A (Alice)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "email": "alice@college.edu",
  "password": "password123",
  "college": "State Engineering College",
  "department": "Computer Science",
  "graduationYear": 2027,
  "bio": "Enthusiastic developer and study group organizer."
}

### Register User B (Bob)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "email": "bob@college.edu",
  "password": "password123",
  "college": "State Engineering College",
  "department": "Computer Science",
  "graduationYear": 2027,
  "bio": "Interested in Competitive Programming and System Design."
}

### Login as Alice (Save Token)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {%
client.global.set("userA_token", response.body.token);
client.global.set("userA_id", response.body.id);
%}

### Login as Bob (Save Token)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {%
client.global.set("userB_token", response.body.token);
client.global.set("userB_id", response.body.id);
%}

### Get Alice's Profile (Using Alice Token)
GET {{host}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}


### =========================================================================
### 2. PEER CONNECTION FLOW
### =========================================================================

### Alice sends connection request to Bob (User ID = 2)
POST {{host}}/api/peers/connect/2
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}

> {%
client.global.set("connection_id", response.body.id);
%}

### Bob views pending requests
GET {{host}}/api/peers/requests
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}

### Bob accepts Alice's connection request
POST {{host}}/api/peers/accept/{{connection_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}

### Alice views list of accepted connections
GET {{host}}/api/peers/connections
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}


### =========================================================================
### 3. FORUM / ASK FOR HELP FLOW
### =========================================================================

### Alice creates a discussion post/help request
POST {{host}}/api/posts
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Need help with Compiler Design",
  "content": "Can anyone explain LALR parsing tables? I am struggling with the state reductions.",
  "category": "Academics"
}

> {%
client.global.set("post_id", response.body.id);
%}

### Bob lists all academic posts
GET {{host}}/api/posts?category=Academics
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}

### Bob posts an answer/comment on Alice's post
POST {{host}}/api/posts/{{post_id}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Check out the Dragon Book, Chapter 4. Reductions happen when there is a dot at the end of the item. Let's schedule a study session!"
}

### Alice retrieves comments for her post
GET {{host}}/api/posts/{{post_id}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}


### =========================================================================
### 4. DOCUMENT SHARING FLOW
### =========================================================================

### Alice uploads a syllabus cheat sheet document
POST {{host}}/api/documents/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

Data Structures Cheat Sheet
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

Important formulas, time complexities, and tree traversals for midterms.
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="department"

Computer Science
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="ds-notes.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Data Structures Midterm Cheat Sheet:
1. BST Search: O(log N) average, O(N) worst.
2. Balanced Trees (AVL/Red-Black): O(log N) always.
3. Graph DFS/BFS: O(V + E) complexity.
--boundary--

> {%
client.global.set("doc_id", response.body.id);
%}

### Bob searches for CS department documents
GET {{host}}/api/documents?department=Computer Science
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}

### Bob downloads the cheat sheet document
GET {{host}}/api/documents/download/{{doc_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}


### =========================================================================
### 5. TEXTBOOK EXCHANGE / BOOK MARKETPLACE FLOW
### =========================================================================

### Alice lists a textbook for sale
POST {{host}}/api/books
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Introduction to Algorithms (CLRS)",
  "author": "Cormen, Leiserson, Rivest, Stein",
  "description": "3rd Edition. Very good condition, no pen marks.",
  "price": 25.0
}

> {%
client.global.set("book_id", response.body.id);
%}

### Bob views available marketplace books
GET {{host}}/api/books
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}

### Bob claims Alice's book listing
POST {{host}}/api/books/{{book_id}}/claim
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}

### Alice verifies her listing is marked unavailable
GET {{host}}/api/books/my
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}


### =========================================================================
### 6. PEER POLL FLOW
### =========================================================================

### Bob creates a poll
POST {{host}}/api/polls
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Which backend stack do you prefer for your main projects?",
  "options": [
    "Spring Boot (Java)",
    "Node.js (JavaScript)",
    "Django (Python)"
  ],
  "expiresAt": "2026-12-31T23:59:59"
}

> {%
// Capture the poll details
client.global.set("poll_id", response.body.id);
client.global.set("option1_id", response.body.options[0].id);
client.global.set("option2_id", response.body.options[1].id);
%}

### Alice fetches all active polls
GET {{host}}/api/polls
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}

### Alice votes for Spring Boot (Option ID 1)
POST {{host}}/api/polls/{{poll_id}}/vote
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "optionId": {{option1_id}}
}

### Alice tries to vote again (Should fail with duplicate warning)
POST {{host}}/api/polls/{{poll_id}}/vote
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "optionId": {{option2_id}}
}


### =========================================================================
### 7. FEST DETAILS & COLLEGE CIRCULARS (REDIS CACHING)
### =========================================================================

### Coordinator lists a college Fest (Triggers Cache Eviction)
POST {{host}}/api/fests
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "TechXplore 2026",
  "description": "Annual national level technical symposium featuring Hackathons, Robotics, and Coding challenges.",
  "location": "Main Campus Auditorium",
  "eventDate": "2026-10-15T09:00:00",
  "coordinatorName": "Prof. Alan Turing",
  "coordinatorEmail": "turing@college.edu"
}

### Fetch Fests: Test Cache Miss (Hits Database & Saves to Redis)
GET {{host}}/api/fests
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}

### Fetch Fests: Test Cache Hit (Loads instantly from Redis cache)
GET {{host}}/api/fests
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}

### Dean creates a new circular notice
POST {{host}}/api/circulars
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Revised Academic Calendar - Semester End",
  "content": "Please note that all semester-end laboratory assessments will be held from Nov 15th to Nov 25th. Theories start Dec 1st.",
  "postedBy": "Dean Academics"
}

### Fetch Circulars: Cache Miss (Loads from database and caches)
GET {{host}}/api/circulars
Authorization: Bearer {{userA_token}}

### Fetch Circulars: Cache Hit (Reads directly from Redis)
GET {{host}}/api/circulars
Authorization: Bearer {{userB_token}}
